The paper discusses the career profile of authors in computer science and physics domains, and focuses on their publication count and citation impact. The paper does not specifically mention any sub-category of computer science, but the topics of citation analysis, author profiling, and prediction of future success suggest that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories such as Computational Complexity (cs.CY), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Software Engineering (cs.SD).
